A: Property Register  This register describes the land and estate comprised in the title.  HILLINGDON 1   (19.07.1973) The Freehold land shown edged with red on the plan of the above Title filed at the Registry and being 26 to 60 (even), Fairfield Road, Uxbridge (UB8 1AL). 2   A Agreement under Seal dated 11 September 1953 made between (1) Robert Spencer Kirby and Frank William Kirby (First Owners) and (2) Arthur Keith Gibbs and Maurice Frank George Gibbs (Second Owners) contains the following provision:- "The Second Owners hereby covenant with the First Owners and the First Owners hereby covenant with the Second Owners in manner following (i) The party wall erected and built as aforesaid as to one longitudinal half thereof and as to the buttresses footings and foundations thereto on the said land of the First Owners and as to the other longitudinal half thereof with the buttresses footings and foundations thereto on the said land of the Second Owners has been erected and constructed as to a party wall to be used for the joint purposes of the said new garage building and any building that may hereafter be erected contiguous to and against such wall by the Second Owners or their successors in title and they the Second Owners and First Owners respectively shall have over and in respect of such wall the rights similar to those given to or conferred upon building and adjoining owners by part VI of the London Building Acts (Amendment) 1939 with respect to party walls within the administrative County of London and falling within the scope of the said Act or rights as near thereto as the circumstances will admit but shall have no further or other rights over or in respect of such wall any rule of law or equity to the contrary notwithstanding (ii) All expenses incurred by the Second Owners and the First Owners respectively in the exercise of their several rights hereunder in respect of the said wall shall be borne and paid by them repectively in the same manner as expenses incurred by building and adjoining owners in respect of party walls falling within the scope of the said Act are thereunder to be borne and paid 2. In further pursuance of the said arrangement and for the considerations aforesaid the First Owners as Personal Representative hereby grant unto the Second Owners and their successors in title in  1 of 5
A: Property Register continued  fee simple the right to maintain as now constructed the eaves on the south eastern side of the said new garage building overhanging the land of the First Owners. 3. And it is hereby agreed and declared that the boundary fence or wall to the rear of the said new garage building between the points marked "B" and "C" on the said plan is the property of and maintainable by the First Owners and their successors in title." NOTE: The land of the first owners is that adjoining the south-eastern title boundary and the land of the second owners is the land in this title.   The party wall referred to lies between the points marked A and B on the filed plan.   The point B referred to is that marked B on the filed plan and point 'C' marks the northernmost point of the south- eastern title boundary. 3   The land edged and numbered in green on the title plan has been removed from this title and registered under the title number or numbers shown in green on the said plan. 4   (06.10.2016) A new title plan based on the latest revision of the Ordnance Survey Map has been prepared.  B: Proprietorship Register  This register specifies the class of title and identifies the owner. It contains any entries that affect the right of disposal.  Title absolute  1   (19.07.1973) PROPRIETOR: ROYLE ESTATES (HODDESDON) LIMITED (Co. Regn. No. 01062669) of 4th Floor, Clerk's Well House, 20 Britton Street, London EC1M 5UA. 2   (05.10.2018) The proprietor's address for service has been changed.  C: Charges Register  This register contains any charges and other matters that affect the land.  1   A Conveyance of the land tinted pink on the filed plan dated 27 November 1868 made between (1) Thomas Coath and (2) William Wills contains covenants details of which are set out in the schedule of restrictive covenants hereto. 2   A Conveyance of the land tinted blue on the filed plan dated 15 January 1869 made between (1) Thomas Coath (2) John Henry Raffety and (3) William Wills contains covenants details of which are set out in the schedule of restrictive covenants hereto. 3   The land is subject to such rights of way, passage and running of water soil gas electricity smoke and fumes, support and protection, entry and other rights as are granted by the leases set out in the schedule of leases hereto. 4   (15.11.2007) UNILATERAL NOTICE affecting 60 Fairfield Road in respect of a notice dated 24 October under Section 42 of the Leasehold Reform, Housing and Urban Development Act 1993. 5   (15.11.2007) BENEFICIARY: NICOLA HAZELTON and SIMON PANNETT (Executors of Alma Juleff Pannett) care of Porter Crossick Solicitors, of 8A Kilburn Bridge, Kilburn High Road, London NW6 6HT.  Schedule of restrictive covenants  1   The following are details of the covenants contained in the Conveyance dated 27 November 1868 referred to in the Charges Register:- "AND the said William Wills doth hereby for himself and his heirs  Title number NGL228210  2 of 5
Schedule of restrictive covenants continued  executors administrators and assigns covenant with the said Thomas Coath his heirs and assigns That he the said William Wills his heirs and assigns will keep observe and perform the said Stipulations of Sale hereinbefore recited or referred to so far as the same respectively relate to the use and enjoyment of the said Two several pieces or parcels of land hereinbefore mentioned to be hereby granted and conveyed or intended so to be That the respective Purchasers should within Three calendar months from the Eleventh day of November instant make and afterwards maintain good and sufficient Fences on the side or sides of their respective Lots as shewn on the said Plan which Fences should not be more than Eight feet high That no Building on several Lots should be erected nearer to the Road or Roads in front than the Building Line shewn on the said Plan and which as to the said Lots 18 and 19 is set back Twenty feet from the south west front against Pages Lane.   That there should not be erected on either of the said Lots (except on Lots 14 and 53) more than two Houses and not on either of the same Lots 14 and 53 more than Four Houses and no House to be erected should be used as a Tavern Public House Beer Shop or as a Shop of any description.   That the Sale of Beer should not be allowed on any Lot That no Bricks should be made or burnt or Brick Kiln used on any Lot That no House to be erected on any of the Lots 1 to 3 inclusive should be of less value than Five hundred pounds on any of the Lots 18 to 24 inclusive of less value than Five hundred pounds on any of the Lots 4 to 17 inclusive of less value than Four hundred pounds on any of the Lots 25 to 31 inclusive of less value than Four hundred pounds on any of the said Lots 32 to 59 inclusive of less value than Three hundred and fifty pounds or on any of the Lots 60 to 76 inclusive of less value than Three hundred pounds The value of a Building to be the amount of its net first cost in material and labor of construction only but these stipulations were not to preclude the purchaser from building Stables or appurtenances to the principal House on any adjoining Lot." NOTE 1: The land tinted pink on the filed plan forms lots 18 and 19 referred to above NOTE 2: Pages Lane referred to above is now known as Harefield Road. 2   The following are details of the covenants contained in the Conveyance dated 15 January 1869 referred to in the Charges Register:- "AND the said William Wills doth hereby for himself his heirs executors administrators and assigns covenant with the said Thomas Coath his heirs and assigns that he the said William Wills his heirs and assigns will keep observe and perform the said stipulations of Sale hereinbefore recited or referred to so far as the same respectively relate to the use and enjoyment of the same piece or parcel of land hereinbefore mentioned to be hereby granted and conveyed or intended so to be.   That the respective purchasers should within three Calendar months from the eleventh day of November one thousand eight hundred and sixty eight make and afterwards maintain good and sufficient fences on the side or sides of their respective Lots as shewn on the said Plan which fences should not be more than eight feet high that no Building on the several Lots should be erected nearer to the Road or Roads in front than the Building Line shewn on the said plan and which as to the said Lot 20 is set back twenty feet from the south west front against Pages Lane that there should not be erected on either of the said Lots (except on Lots 14 and 53) more than two houses and not on either of the same Lots 14 and 53 more than five houses and no house to be erected should be used as a Tavern Public House Beer shop or as a Shop of any description that the sale of Beer should not be allowed on any Lot that no bricks should be made or burnt or brick kiln used on any Lot that no house to be erected on any of the Lots 1 to 3 inclusive should be of less value than Five hundred pounds on any of the Lots 18 to 24 inclusive of less value than Five hundred pounds on any of the Lots 4 to 17 inclusive of less value than Four hundred pounds on any of the Lots 25 to 31 inclusive of less value than Four hundred pounds on any of the said Lots 32 to 59 inclusive of less value than Three hundred and fifty pounds or on any of the Lots 60 to 76 inclusive of less value than Three hundred pounds that the value of a Building should be the amount of its net first cost in material and labour of construction only but the stipulations were not to preclude the purchaser from building stables or appurtenances to the principal house on any adjoining Lot."
